//
Node vs JS:

 

NodeJS allows Javascript code to run outside a browser, it is essentially an environment.
Doesn't have the capability to add HTML tags, because it doesn't need to.
NodeJS is essentially the V8 Javascript engine bundled with other useful libraries for I/O and networking.
JS vs Node:

 

Javascript is a programming language by itself.
Javascript has the ability to interact with the DOM and HTML elements.
Javascript (while being run in a browser) has alot of useful variables such as "document" that make interaction with the browser and it's services much easier